\par }{\b\f1\fs20 --[Notes]-}{\f1\fs20 
\par 
\par -Certain maps in World War III have been designed with the player slots in the wrong order. You can tell these maps because they have irregular team colour assignments (normally player slot 1 is yellow, slot 2 is red, 3 green, 4 blue, 
etc.). Using these maps may result in odd alliances.
\par 
\par -Using "Random Positions" will also mix up the Alliance process. This could be good fun if all slots are filled though, as you don't know who you'll be allied with.
\par 
\par -The console stats, such as "Bounties Collected" and "Units destroyed" are totalled for all players, and are not personal stats. In addition, they don't update until they next appear (this is to improve performance).
\par 
